          <p class="text-gray-700">No direct migration. You'd rebuild from scratch. Mixo doesn't export code. If you think you might need Framer's design quality or code export later, start with Framer. Migration pain is real.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Which loads faster?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Framer. My tests: Framer ~0.7s, Mixo ~1.1s. Both pass Core Web Vitals, but Framer's performance is exceptional. If speed is critical, Framer wins.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Do both support custom domains?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Yes. Both connect custom domains on paid plans. No meaningful difference here. Framer: connect in dashboard. Mixo: connect in settings. Both work reliably.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Which has better SEO?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Framer loads faster (better for Core Web Vitals). Mixo is SEO-optimized but slower. In practice: both can rank. Framer has technical edge. Mixo is easier to use for SEO beginners.</p>
